Installation Requirements
    Node.js and npm:

    Ensure you have Node.js installed. npm comes bundled with Node.js, so youâ€™ll have access to both.
    MySQL:

Install MySQL server. 
    You can download it from the MySQL official site. Or try use xamp
    Configure the MySQL server with the following details:
    Host: localhost
    User: root
    Password: KuzivasMysql@2003
    Database: Zim_Tour
    Ensure that the MySQL service is running.

Next.js:

    If not already installed, you can create a new Next.js project using the following command:
    
    npx create-next-app@latest

Project Dependencies:

Navigate to your project directory in the terminal and run:

npm install
This command will install all the necessary dependencies listed in your package.json file.
Running the Application:

After installing dependencies, you can start the application with:

npm run dev

Your application will typically be accessible at http://localhost:3000.

Extensions 

1) ES7+ React/Redux/React-Native snippets
2) HTML CSS Support
3) JavaScript (ES6) code snippets
4) JavaScript and TypeScript Nightly
